147984.name: Prevalence of wasting, weight for height (% of children under 5)
147984.description: Prevalence of wasting is the proportion of children under age 5 whose weight for height is more than two standard deviations below the median for the international reference population ages 0-59.

source.name: UNICEF, World Health Organization and World Bank
source.dataPublisherSource: Joint child malnutrition estimates - UNICEF / World Health Organization / World Bank
